# Conductor: Backend

## Project Structure

- `auth/`: Authentication handler + encompassing gateway
- `database/`: Prisma schema, migrations, and database client setup
- `tickets/`: Feature module implementing Conductor endpoints
- `encore.gen/, .encore/`: Encore-generated code, created by running encore dev (or pnpm dev) (do not edit manually)

## Encore

### Commands

1. Start Encore: `encore run`
2. Fresh connection URLs: `encore db conn-uri conductor-db` and `encore db conn-uri conductor-db --shadow`
3. Check for compile-time errors: `encore check`

## Prisma

### Generate

Use `prisma generate` whenever you change your Prisma schema, so your Prisma Client stays in sync with your schema

```bash
cd backend/<service>
npx prisma generate --schema=./prisma/schema.prisma
```

<!--     "postinstall": "npx prisma generate --schema=./backend/database/prisma/schema.prisma"
 -->

### Migrations

Use `prisma migrate dev` when you make changes to your Prisma schema and want to update your database schema, keeping a migration history

```bash
cd backend/database
npx prisma migrate dev --name init --schema=./prisma/schema.prisma
```

#### Generate New Migrations

When you make changes to your schema.prisma file:

```bash
cd backend/database
npx prisma migrate dev --name describe-your-change --schema=./prisma/schema.prisma

```

# Reset the `auth` schema

```bash
psql "$postgresql://conductor-ee92:local@127.0.0.1:9500/tickets?sslmode=disable" -v ON_ERROR_STOP=1 <<'SQL'
SET search_path = public;
DROP SCHEMA IF EXISTS auth CASCADE;
CREATE SCHEMA auth;
SQL
```

```bash
# Reset the `tickets` schema (do similarly, if needed)
psql "$BASEpostgresql://conductor-ee92:local@127.0.0.1:9500/tickets?sslmode=disable_URL" -v ON_ERROR_STOP=1 <<'SQL'
SET search_path = public;
DROP SCHEMA IF EXISTS tickets CASCADE;
CREATE SCHEMA tickets;
SQL

```
